{"about_the_game":"Toroban is an infinitely wrapping puzzle game. Explore a nonlinear overworld full of interconnected puzzles. There are various biomes to experience, each with a unique mechanic and theme.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Tutorial</h2>This is the starting area, which contains toroidal puzzles with blocks, buttons, and gates.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/extras/tutorial.gif?t=1727638935\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Regions</h2>The walls have crumbled in this area, allowing access to puzzles from the outside world. Objects can be transferred between puzzles. Players must alternate between activating the toroidal puzzles and interacting with the puzzles from the outside world.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/extras/regions.gif?t=1727638935\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Offsets</h2>This area contains X and Y axis blocks, that when moved, shift the alignment of the toroidal grid.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/extras/offsets.png?t=1727638935\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Toros</h2>The characters in Toroban are called Toros. There can be multiple Toros in a puzzle, and this area explores the concepts of how they can work together to solve puzzles. The same colored Toros strongly stick together. Multiple Toros pushing together are stronger and can push more objects at once.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/extras/toros.png?t=1727638935\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Infinity</h2>In this area, some objects are finite instead of infinite like in previous areas. The interactions between finite and infinite objects can result in special states that are used to solve puzzles.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/extras/infinity.png?t=1727638935\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Advanced</h2>The final area containing puzzles with all the mechanics combined!","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1727638935","background_raw":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/page_bg_generated.jpg?t=1727638935","capsule_image":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/capsule_231x87.jpg?t=1727638935","capsule_imagev5":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/capsule_184x69.jpg?t=1727638935","categories":[{"description":"Single-player","id":2},{"description":"Partial Controller Support","id":18}],"content_descriptors":{"ids":[],"notes":null},"detailed_description":"Toroban is an infinitely wrapping puzzle game. Explore a nonlinear overworld full of interconnected puzzles. There are various biomes to experience, each with a unique mechanic and theme.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Tutorial</h2>This is the starting area, which contains toroidal puzzles with blocks, buttons, and gates.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/extras/tutorial.gif?t=1727638935\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Regions</h2>The walls have crumbled in this area, allowing access to puzzles from the outside world. Objects can be transferred between puzzles. Players must alternate between activating the toroidal puzzles and interacting with the puzzles from the outside world.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/extras/regions.gif?t=1727638935\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Offsets</h2>This area contains X and Y axis blocks, that when moved, shift the alignment of the toroidal grid.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1961850/extras/offsets.png?t=1727638935\" /><h2